{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, attention-guided pipelines that couple defect detection with error-triggering have shown promise in creating closed-loop testing scenarios [158].",
    "Instead of random generation, such agents can first analyze critical or recently changed modules to formulate a comprehensive plan.",
    "This architecture enables the LLM to function as a virtual test engineer, systematically improving the quality of the test suite.To address increasingly complex tasks and the inherent issue of hallucinations in LLMs, collaborative multi-agent frameworks have emerged.",
    "CANDOR [147] assigns tasks such as test planning, code generation, validation, and assertion repair to agents with distinct roles, effectively mitigating hallucinations in assertion generation through a consensus mechanism resembling an \"expert panel discussion\".",
    "Other multi-agent frameworks demonstrate enhanced adaptive repair capabilities, where agents utilize iterative feedback to not only modify test cases but also dynamically adjust the program under test itself, ensuring alignment between code and requirement specifications [82]."
  ]
}